Name: schizophreniform disorder
Definition: A psychotic disorder that involves schizophrenia symptoms over time period of one month.

Name: schizoaffective disorder
Definition: A psychotic disorder that is characterized by recurring episodes of mood fluctuations and a loss of contact with reality.
Synonym: relapsed small cell carcinoma of the lung

Name: schizophrenia
Definition: A psychotic disorder that is characterized by a disintegration of thought processes and of emotional responsiveness.

Name: delusional disorder
Definition: A psychotic disorder that involves an uncommon psychiatric condition in which patients present with circumscribed symptoms of non-bizarre delusions

Name: obsolete mixed choriocarcinoma and embryonal carcinoma of the testis
Definition: A psychotic disorder that involves an uncommon psychiatric condition in which patients present with circumscribed symptoms of non-bizarre delusions
Synonym: mixed Choriocarcinoma and Embryonal carcinoma of testis

Name: substance-induced psychosis
Definition: A vein disease that is characterized by inflammation of a vein.
